Machine Learning Workflow Project Report
Project Title
Machine Learning Workflow for Customer Churn Prediction
1. Problem Statement
The objective of this project is to build and evaluate machine learning models that predict whether a customer is likely to leave a service. Customer churn prediction helps businesses identify at-risk customers and improve customer retention strategies.
2. Dataset
Dataset Name: Telco Customer Churn Dataset
Source: Kaggle
The dataset contains customer demographic information, account details, service usage, and churn status. It includes both numerical and categorical features suitable for supervised machine learning.
3. Data Preprocessing
The following preprocessing steps were performed:
Removed duplicate records.
Handled missing values using appropriate methods.
Encoded categorical variables using Label Encoding and One-Hot Encoding.
Scaled numerical features using StandardScaler.
Split the dataset into training and testing sets.
These steps ensured the data was clean and ready for model training.
4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Exploratory Data Analysis was performed to understand the dataset and identify important patterns.
The following visualizations were created:
Correlation Heatmap
Target Class Distribution
Feature Distribution Histogram
Box Plot for Outlier Detection
The analysis showed that some features had a strong relationship with customer churn, while class imbalance was moderate.
5. Machine Learning Models
Two machine learning algorithms were implemented:
Model 1: Logistic Regression
Simple and interpretable baseline model.
Fast training time.
Good performance for binary classification.
Model 2: Random Forest Classifier
Ensemble learning algorithm.
Better captures complex relationships.
Higher prediction accuracy than Logistic Regression.
6. Model Evaluation
Evaluation metrics used:
Accuracy
Precision
Recall
F1-Score
ROC-AUC Score
The Random Forest model achieved better overall performance compared to Logistic Regression because it handled feature interactions more effectively.
7. Business Insights
The trained model can help organizations identify customers who are likely to churn.
This enables businesses to:
Improve customer retention.
Offer personalized promotions.
Reduce revenue loss.
Increase customer satisfaction.
Make data-driven business decisions.
8. Conclusion
This project demonstrated the complete machine learning workflow, including data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis, model training, and evaluation.
Among the implemented models, Random Forest produced better predictive performance than Logistic Regression. The project highlights how supervised machine learning can solve real-world business problems through accurate prediction and data-driven insights.
